description:
A furious Daredevil clashes with Mole Man as the forces of Megacrime assemble!

By Mark Waid and Paolo Rivera.

Plus: The horror called Hybrid is feeding off the students of Avengers Academy - but why is Reptil helping him?!

By Chirstos Gage, Tom Raney and Tom Grummett.

Includes material reprinted from Daredevil #10-10.1 and Avengers Academy #23-24

Lady Death is ever a woman of contradictions, and with good reason. The Blood of Heaven & Hell runs through her veins. In this, the collected version of her second mini-series, the saga of the ravishing seductress of The Netherworld continues.

Since Lady Death conquered Lucifer, the Father of Lies, she's ruled Hell with an iron fist for over 400 years. But the mental manipulations of the sensual and vampiric PURGATORI, reveal that Lady Death was just his pawn. Learning the whole truth of her tortured past—and Lucifer's role in it—Lady Death surrenders to the darkness and becomes the voracious Lady Demon. The explosive finale—where Lady Death battles Lucifer—is played on a grand, epic scale and unlocks her true destiny for once and for all.
name: Between Heaven & Hell

deck: Pipil Kahn has a foolproof plan how to put Groo six feet under.  Unfortunately for him, it may be that no plan is foolproof enough to thwart Groo.
description: There's no accounting for taste. That must be why so many accountants are buying Groo collections! This trade paperback collects the latest and greatest adventures of Groo, the world's stupidest barbarian. In a savage land of another era, a goodly segment of the world has long been under the heavy thumb of the evil, power-mad despot known as Pipil Khan. The tyrant wants nothing more than to name an heir and shuck his mortal coil, but one thing stands in his way: Groo! It seems Khan just can't rest easy until Groo is out of the way. He'll give his kingdom to the one of his sons who can accomplish this. One of them has a foolproof plan how to do it. Unfortunately for him, it may be that no plan is foolproof enough to thwart Groo. Eisner Award-winning cartoonist Sergio Aragonés and "World's Greatest Soccer Mom" Award-winning wordsmith Mark Evanier bring you more moronic mayhem from the barbarian who made "mulch" a household word.
name: TPB

deck: The second semester and the year end project.
description:
The Knights who no longer say "Ni" ! (Les Chevaliers qui ne font plus "Ni" !)

(A reference to Monthy Pythons Holy Grail Movie and The Knights who say Ni)

Second semester: for their end of year project the students need to draw up a scheme that aims to conquer the world. They need to prove that the scheme is executable to get their grades. Our trio decides on making living biscuit soldiers (from cookies taken from the army that are so hard to eat that they are virtually indestructible). The project nearly gets out of control when some of the living coockies rebel. During the presentation of the different projects, a team of Saint-Ange intervenes, with the approval of the Dean of the FEAH, to counter the evil plans of the FEAH students. It seems that the students have fallen into a trap?

  • Chapter VI Au loup! (To the wolf!)
  • ChapterVII La Recette magique (The magical Recipe)
  • Chapter VIII Le Puits de science (The pitts of science)
  • Chapter IX Rosebud (refers to the movie Citizen Kane)
  • Chapter X La Dernière Chance au dernier moment (The last Chance at the last moment)
name: Les Chevaliers qui ne font plus

deck: A duel on life and death between FEAH and Saint-Ange.
description:
The Tango of Death (Le Tango de la Mort)

The media war between FEAH and Saint-Ange continues with a duel between Ange and Chance. Xiong Mao and Ombre are charged by Funérailles to forge a weapon (a blade) for Chance that rivals his sword Claidheamor, otherwise she will not survice the duel. Meanwhile, Val, Sablon and Funérailles train Chance in battle and swordmanship. Their goal is to raise the popularity of FEAH, which has fallen to an all time low, now that Saint-Ange has passed them off as a school for villains.

  • Chapter XI La mort du héros (The Death of the hero)
  • Chapter XII L'au-delà du bien est du mal (The hereafter of the bad and the good)
  • Chapter XIII Lame des guerrières (The blade of the warriors)
  • Chapter XIV Chaud time ! (Litteraly Hot times, but pronouced as Showtime ! )
name: Le Tango de la Mort

deck: The start of the second year, the students take controle.
description:
Succube Pizza

After an intense battle, Chance defeats Ange and becomes the most popular girl of the academy. She discovers taht the Dean is Funérailles brother. Her promotion, and those of her friends, to the second year is no longer an issue. The start of the second year is eventful: an attempted kidnapping and assasination of the Dean, a seizure of power by the students, departures, defectors, newcomers... Our trio have started a small business called Succubus Pizza (selling Pizzas what else), that will be challenged by these events.
name: Succube Pizza

deck: On the origin of the academy and our heros.
description:
Nanorigines

After the assassination attempts on the dean of FEAH and the revolt of the students, the university resumes its education as normally as possible. For once is seems that everything will go as it should be, at least not until Sablon discovers that the rival school of Saint-Ange has devised yet another plot to shut down FEAH. They have used their polical influence to have the politcal world draw up a bill to reduce the number of superhero-schools. The only solution to save FEAH is to prove that it has existed for over 50 years. While the other students mount protests in the streets to slow down the voting, Chance, Xiong Mao and Ombre plunge into a investigation to reconstruct the history of their university. They seek the aid of a student of the third year to find the former Dean. In the midst of their investigation someone wipes their memory clean and they no longer know who they are. Now they no only need to find the orgins of the school but also themselves. To complicate matters a giant Legofigure wreaks havoc in the streets.
name: Nanorigines
